What:		/sys/devices/platform/*pcie/*/l1ss/l1ss_force
Date:		July 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6.30-android15-8
Description:
		Control the L1SS override for the cpif driver.  Writing a
		1, on, yes will enable the L1SS override feature.  Writing
		a 0, off or no will disable the L1SS override.  The L1SS
		override feature will restrict the L1SS states that the
		endpoint is configured for.

		When enabled, only L1 state is enabled.  Other L1 substates
		may be enabled via the l11_enable and l12_enable sysfs

What:		/sys/devices/platform/*pcie/*/l1ss/l11_enable
Date:		July 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6.30-android15-8
Description:
		Control the L1.1 PCIe L1SS substate.  Only takes affect when
		l1ss_force sysfs is alaso enabled.  Writing a 1, on, yes
		will configure the endpoint allow entering the L1.1 substate
		Writing a 0, off or no will prevent the endpoint from
		entering the L1.1 substate.

What:		/sys/devices/platform/*pcie/*/l1ss/l12_enable
Date:		July 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6.30-android15-8
Description:
		Control the L1.2 PCIe L1SS substate.  Only takes affect when
		l1ss_force sysfs is alaso enabled.  Writing a 1, on, yes
		will configure the endpoint allow entering the L1.2 substate
		Writing a 0, off or no will prevent the endpoint from
		entering the L1.1 substate.
